{"TopicId":210053,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Mods for special scale parts?","CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-09T22:09:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Rutabaga22","CreatedById":221143,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-09T22:09:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there any mods for tanks at the scale of BDB parts?(3.125, 1.5, 0.938, 6.5, etc.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Probird_23","CreatedById":222216,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-09T22:16:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUniversal storage 2 and Tantares do have BDB scale parts, not sure about any other mods though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeadJohn","CreatedById":201293,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-10T02:43:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Knes mod (European rockets) has some 0.938 tanks and other parts. It\u0027s a lot of parts if all you want are tanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsider the Tweakscale mod if it\u0027s not incompatible with your other mods. That will let you turn stock tanks into different sizes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bigyihsuan","CreatedById":29291,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-11T14:07:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProcedural Parts, as usual, is good for getting tanks of any diameter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI recommend this patch so it\u0027s a little easier to get tot the sizes BDB uses often (0.938, 1.835, 3.125, mostly)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-perl prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E@PART\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[*]:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EHAS\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E@MODULE\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EProceduralPart\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]]:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EAFTER\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EProceduralParts\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E@MODULE\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E[\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EProceduralPart\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E]\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E{\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E%\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EdiameterLargeStep \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E0.625\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E%\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EdiameterSmallStep \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E=\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022lit\u0022\u003E0.15625\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\t\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis patch will make the size changes based on 1.25m. Small step is 1/8th of 1.25m, and large step is 1/2 of 1.25m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the Sarnus/Saturn parts, you will need to manually change the size to 4.25m since it\u0027s not a multiple of 1.25m, but for all other parts it will work great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}